We're going to plan a feature.

The feature document is kept in @feature.md

A feature plan has three sections:

0. context
1. requirements
2. considerations
3. tasks
- [ ] this task is not done
- ✅ this task is done

Context is information that is useful in the near term
If requirements are not clear, prompt the user for clarification
If considerations are not illuminating enough, prompt the user for clarification
If a task is ready to be worked on, prompt the user to allow starting it

As you go, keep modifying the sections of the feature plan. Add and truncate sections as makes sense.

When working on a task, prompt the user if they'd like to make a git commit frequently. Execute this in the terminal.